A RESOLUTION
1 Commending the emergency medical services professionals of Georgia and recognizing
2 February 28, 2025, as Emergency Medical Services Recognition Day at the state capitol; and
3 for other purposes.
4 WHEREAS, Georgia's emergency medical services (EMS) system is celebrating its 49th year
5 of service; and
6 WHEREAS, the emergency medical services professionals of Georgia respond to almost one
7 million calls for assistance annually, risking their lives on a daily basis to go to the aid of
8 those in need; and
9 WHEREAS, in the State of Georgia, there are more than 26,000 licensed emergency medical
10 services personnel who provide the essential life-saving services associated with
11 out-of-hospital emergency medical care; and
12 WHEREAS, the goals and services of each of these individuals include illness and injury
13 prevention; trauma system development; public information and education; prompt, efficient,
14 and effective delivery of pre-hospital emergency medical care; transportation to the most
