15 appropriate receiving facility; and other activities related to the health and well-being of the
16 citizens of Georgia; and
17 WHEREAS, EMS personnel provide access to quality pre-hospital emergency care that
18 dramatically improves the survival and recovery rate of persons stricken with sudden illness
19 or injury.
20 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
21 commend the emergency medical services professionals of Georgia for their outstanding and
22 courageous service to this state and recognize February 28, 2025, as Emergency Medical
23 Services Recognition Day at the state capitol.
24 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
25 to make appropriate copies of this resolution available for distribution to Chad Black,
26 Chairman of the Georgia Emergency Medical Services Association, and Michael Johnson,
27 Director of the Georgia Office of Emergency Medical Services and Trauma of the
28 Department of Public Health.
